Month = {JAN 4},
Abstract = {Social attachment can explain well the bond between users and social
   media, but existing research lacks measures of social attachment scales.
   To this end, this study takes attachment theory as the basis for scale
   development. On the basis of the development of multidimensional scales
   for adult, brand, and local attachment, it combines existing relevant
   studies on social attachment, selects three representative social media
   such as TikTok, WeChat, and MicroBlog as theoretical samples, explores
   the concept and structure of social attachment, and develops a social
   attachment scale through qualitative interviews and open-ended
   questionnaires. This study applied SPSS 24.0 and Mplus 7.0 to test the
   social attachment scale. The findings reveal that social attachment
   consists of three constructs: social connection, social dependence and
