   thinking style or worldview. Validation of the DTI was explored with
   regard to the relationships among dichotomous thinking, borderline
   personality, narcissism, self-esteem, undervaluing others, intolerance
   for ambiguity, perfectionism, and the Big Five; and relationships
   between dichotomous thinking and peer ratings of traits and attitudes.
   Factor analysis of the DTI revealed 3 components: preference for
   dichotomy, dichotomous beliefs, and profit-and-loss thinking. Internal
   consistency and test-retest reliability of the DTI were at a sufficient
   level. Correlations among self-measures supported the convergent and
