   results in schadenfreude. However, LBA did not have any significant
   impact on schadenfreude. The moderating influence of CNFU is partially
   supported. This research further confirms that consumers' public
   consumption has more relevance to visible social comparison and
   potential feelings of malicious envy towards others. Practical
   implications The research model may work as a strategic tool to
   identify, which group of consumers (e.g. high vs low attachment)
